default4.1
default              
defaultBTP plays an important role in response to severe weather on the rail transport network.  In o
defaultrder to maximise the value of w
defaulthat BTP do, it is essential that BTP work in partnership with others.  In this respect, BTP has worked hard to ensure that we, 
defaultas a national police service, are better connected with Lo
defaultcal Resilience F
defaultorums around the country, in order to fully understand the impacts of severe weather and demonstrate how we can effectively contribute to the minimisation of disruption to the Rail n
defaultetwork during such severe weather episodes.
default&#xa0;
default4.2
default              
defaultAt present there is still an independence of operation in response to severe weather across the transport groups
default:
default Rail, Road, Aviation and Maritime.  
defaultDuring the Summer 2012 Olympics, the DfT set up a cross-m
defaultodal transport group, led by BTP, to plan and deliver a safe Games for those travelling.  
defaultThe group delivered a mechanism of understanding how each of the modal forms of transport would contribute to the movement of those travelling to the games and enable
defaultd a co-ordinated approach to be undertaken.  For transport-related disruption, such a cross-modal group could have benefits in ensuring the minimisation of disruption in times of severe weather.
